h3cVoiceGeneral.name: h3cVoiceGeneral

revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB file.

h3cVoiceGeneral.contactinfo: PLAT Team Huawei 3Com Technologies co.,Ltd. Shang-Di Information Industry Base, Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.huawei-3com.com Zip:100085
h3cVoiceGeneral.description: This MIB is to provide the definition of voice voice general configuration.

h3cVoGeneralJitterLen.name: h3cVoGeneralJitterLen
h3cVoGeneralJitterLen.description: This object indicates the length of the Jitter buffer.

h3cVoGeneralMatchPolicy.name: h3cVoGeneralMatchPolicy
h3cVoGeneralMatchPolicy.description: This object indicates the policy of number matching.

h3cVoGeneralDataStatistics.name: h3cVoGeneralDataStatistics
h3cVoGeneralDataStatistics.description: This object indicates whether the data statistics is enabled.

h3cVoGeneralDialTerminator.name: h3cVoGeneralDialTerminator
h3cVoGeneralDialTerminator.description: This object indicates the global character, which is used to notify gateway that dialing is completed.

h3cVoGeneralCallStart.name: h3cVoGeneralCallStart
h3cVoGeneralCallStart.description: This object indicates whether to support the FAST START mode which the caller side initiates.

h3cVoGeneralCalledTunnel.name: h3cVoGeneralCalledTunnel
h3cVoGeneralCalledTunnel.description: This object indicates whether the called tunnel function is enabled.

h3cVoGeneralSpecialService.name: h3cVoGeneralSpecialService
h3cVoGeneralSpecialService.description: This object indicates whether special service number function is enabled.

h3cVoGeneralPeerSearchStop.name: h3cVoGeneralPeerSearchStop
h3cVoGeneralPeerSearchStop.description: This object indicates the maximum amount of the entities which the system will scan when a call has been initiated.

h3cVoGeneralPeerSelectOrderRule.name: h3cVoGeneralPeerSelectOrderRule
h3cVoGeneralPeerSelectOrderRule.description: This object indicates the rule order applied in voice entity selection. epr(1) --- explicit match, priority, random epl(2) --- explicit match, priority, longest no use elp(3) --- explicit match, longest no use, priority elr(4) --- explicit match, longest no use, random per(5) --- priority, explicit match, random pel(6) --- priority, explicit match, longest no use ple(7) --- priority, longest no use, explicit match plr(8) --- priority, longest no use, random lep(9) --- longest no use, explicit match, priority ler(10) --- longest no use, explicit match, random lpe(11) --- longest no use, priority, explicit match lpr(12) --- longest no use, priority, random er(13) --- explicit match, random pr(14) --- priority, random lr(15) --- longest no use, random explicitMatch(16) --- explicit match priority(17) --- priority random(18) --- random longestNoUse(19) --- longest no use ep(20) --- explicit match, priority el(21) --- explicit match, longest no use pe(22) --- priority, explicit match pl(23) --- priority, longest no use le(24) --- longest no use, explicit match lp(25) --- longest no use, priority

h3cVoGeneralPeerSelectTypePriority.name: h3cVoGeneralPeerSelectTypePriority
h3cVoGeneralPeerSelectTypePriority.description: This object indicates the priority-ranked type of voice entity. 1ST 2DN 3RD noneType(1) --- NONE TYPE voipPotsVofr(2) --- VOIP POTS VOFR voipVofrPots(3) --- VOIP VOFR POTS potsVoipVofr(4) --- POTS VOIP VOFR potsVofrVoip(5) --- POTS VOFR VOIP vofrPotsVoip(6) --- VOFR POTS VOIP vofrVoipPots(7) --- VOFR VOIP POTS

h3cVoGeneralDscpSignal.name: h3cVoGeneralDscpSignal
h3cVoGeneralDscpSignal.description: This object indicates DSCP(Different Service Code Point) signal value.

h3cVoGeneralDscpMedia.name: h3cVoGeneralDscpMedia
h3cVoGeneralDscpMedia.description: This object indicates DSCP(Different Service Code Point) media value.

h3cVoNumSubstTable.name: h3cVoNumSubstTable
h3cVoNumSubstTable.description: The table contains the number substitute rule.

h3cVoNumSubstIndex.name: h3cVoNumSubstIndex
h3cVoNumSubstIndex.description: The index of the number substitute rule table.

h3cVoNumSubstFirstRule.name: h3cVoNumSubstFirstRule
h3cVoNumSubstFirstRule.description: This object indicates the first rule to be used.

h3cVoNumSubstDotMatchRule.name: h3cVoNumSubstDotMatchRule
h3cVoNumSubstDotMatchRule.description: This object indicates the dot wildcard match rule. endOnly - only end of E.164 number (input format) leftRight - match form left to right (input format) rightLeft - match form right to left (input format)

h3cVoNumSubstRowStatus.name: h3cVoNumSubstRowStatus
h3cVoNumSubstRowStatus.description: This object is used to create, delete or modify a row in this table.

h3cVoNumSubstRuleTable.name: h3cVoNumSubstRuleTable
h3cVoNumSubstRuleTable.description: The table contains the number-substitute rule information.

h3cVoNumSubstRuleEntry.name: h3cVoNumSubstRuleEntry
h3cVoNumSubstRuleEntry.description: The entry of a single number substitute rule.

h3cVoNumSubstRuleIndex.name: h3cVoNumSubstRuleIndex
h3cVoNumSubstRuleIndex.description: The index of a number-substitute rule.

h3cVoNumSubstRuleInputFormat.name: h3cVoNumSubstRuleInputFormat
h3cVoNumSubstRuleInputFormat.description: This object specifies the match format for input.

h3cVoNumSubstRuleOutputFormat.name: h3cVoNumSubstRuleOutputFormat
h3cVoNumSubstRuleOutputFormat.description: This object specifies the output format.

h3cVoNumSubstRuleRowStatus.name: h3cVoNumSubstRuleRowStatus
h3cVoNumSubstRuleRowStatus.description: This object is used to create, delete or modify a row in this table.

h3cVoMaxCallTable.name: h3cVoMaxCallTable
h3cVoMaxCallTable.description: The table contains the maximum number of the calls which can be established simultaneously.

h3cVoMaxCallEntry.name: h3cVoMaxCallEntry
h3cVoMaxCallEntry.description: The entry of the max call table.

h3cVoMaxCallTableIndex.name: h3cVoMaxCallTableIndex
h3cVoMaxCallTableIndex.description: The index uniquely identifies a single maximum call value.

h3cVoMaxCallValue.name: h3cVoMaxCallValue
h3cVoMaxCallValue.description: This object specifies a single maximum call value.

h3cVoMaxCallTableRowStatus.name: h3cVoMaxCallTableRowStatus
h3cVoMaxCallTableRowStatus.description: This object is used to create, delete or modify a row in this table. Note: when create a new row, h3cVoMaxCallValue must be configured.
